Rushden - I call it Rusden, it's Rushden, but it's a - see they - down there we call girls we call 'em wenches, I - well there's all different - there's different ways in talking down there. It's all I know it's Rusden and Wellingborough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 And when did you move to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Luton
{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Oh 1903, 1904 - 1904.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Where abouts did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 
We come down to a road what we knew as Dukes Street, and - father was on a building site in the new road called Hartley Road, that's - about ten minutes walk aw
ay, and they were just laying the kerbs, of course I was a little kiddie just as high as that table and up and down the brick work and all that, I loved it. And - in a few days - oh you got to school, how old are you you know, a big chap come to me, and -
 told mum, I had to go to school with my three - three sisters. Want to know what was living with us and - of course some was living with the other relations close by and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 How many were there in the family then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Oh fourteen of us altogether - n
o, ten then. We had a - mother had four more - in - Hartley Road, not Hartley Road, in Berrypark. That's another part of the town. Not far from here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Can you tell me how they came in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Oh I don't know, I know the last - the last - moth
er had one in - Warwick Road, one in Hartley Road - and four in Berwick Park, that's as far as I know. And they're all sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 All sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Were you the only boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 I - I was - I was the only one that kept - you know, kept going, 
the other sisters - I had one brother, twins, they were a girl and boy, and they just passed away about a fortnight or so afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 After they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 That's right. Fortnight after they were born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 So how many survived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Well four 
- thirteen of us, you can count - I can count the thirteen of us. I can remember ten - eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 All girls except you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Can you remember their names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Oh - Lizzie, Frances Anna, she lives in the town now, she's seventy-eight.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 What name was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Florence Hannah. Lives up - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Napier Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, in her own - well - retired. And - the next one is Betty, what's alive, she's in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Viscot Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And I've got another one, Susan, and she lives down Maldon. That's the only ones I was - you know - just left. But - to go through the whole family theres {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Elizabeth{\*\xmlclose}
, Hannah - well, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Florence{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Flo we call her, Florence Hannah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 This is from the eldest down is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 That's right, down, then myself, but I'm not talking about the passed
 away ones, they're - do you want them in as well? Passed away. Well - there's Ruth between me and Flo, Ruth and May. They - one died in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Berwick{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and one died in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Hartley Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Then there comes myself, then Bessie, Rose, Sue and Naomi. Naomi. We call Nomi, yes, short. Me mother's name was Omi. So you see it - Nay - Naomi, we - well just carry on Naomi. That's in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 How many years were there between you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Well, near as I can tell you as far as - well see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 About two was it?
