trade so I'll give him a trade, well, put him to a trade - upholsterer. And after about six weeks there - he come home - oh hello, bronchial trouble again. So he kept in coughing and spitting about and I said, all right, pack up. I said, we'll go up and s
e
e Doctor Ackthorpe, up the road, and - he said, what's the boy doing? I said, upholstery. He said, take him away quick. And he gives some medicine for bronchial trouble, and - after a few weeks - you know, walking about the streets with nothing to do and 
-
 he's getting fed up, I said, why don't you try - in the paper trade or - milkman. I said, you're thick and heavy, I said, you'll do a milkman. Unbeknown he went to the Co-op and got a job and - he was there five or six year. Then he went in the building 
t
