Me, thirteen. Yes. There was the throat trouble round the town then here, and I did have a sore throat and - of course we didn't know - and - I said to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1444406  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 I said - two or three days I said, there's something on my th
roat mum. I had to gargle me throat with condis fluid, if you know what that is don't you. Condis fluid, yes. Potash, now what's the other word?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Permanganate of potash?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10055362 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 You've got it. We called it condis fluid. Yes. That's very - well you like t
o keep a bottle of it by you, for cuts, throat trouble, or anything in that way. Mixed up ready, keep a bottle by you. That's better than a chemists shop. That's what we was told from as kids. We had to keep it by us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16147787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8718839\charrsid1444406 Were you sorry that you left school or were you happy to leave?
