Well deary now - you put it this way, I supposed to had - I had a - what we called the dip down the throat to see there's something wrong, 'cos I had a sore throat and I wouldn't let 'em touch my throat. I did have a so
re throat, it was all - inflamed. And - I done a bunk for hour or two, you know, didn't go to school I - went on a field somewhere, on a farm then to see some house, 'cos I knew there was something wrong then and I didn't want anybody interfere with me, a
nd - fortnight, three weeks, all the time - \{BLANK\}
 and - dad come in with it and - they said, where you been boy? School dad. He said, come here. Then - the signal went up, me uncle give me a signal, and - I'm sorry to tell - I'm sorry dad, but I said, but
 I've been over Lingbury on a farm, collecting eggs. I said, so I could earn myself a penny. And - he touched me here. Oh, I said, don't. He said, now tell the doctor in front room and the policeman, he said, tell them what's the matter. I got a sore thro
a
t. I'd tonsillitis. And we didn't know what it was. And - well you can tell me with me speech at that time, I was just feel clogged up, but as soon as I had a - condis fluid, drop of that down me, cleaned me throat I was right as ninepence. I had - then t
his for about four or five months I did, I was supposed to go back to school but I went back to work. And I was thirteen.
